 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/uxazymt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XazyMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/1/02 7:15:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=352.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 8th Shawl</span><hr size=1> Well I did it with mass overkill of forces a solid good group or two of 60's probably can do it no problem, but I would always advice to bring extra people since if you fail you have to redo all the combines.  Avoid bringing KOS people, have an enchanter to memblur in case someone agroes him.  Mobs are all unsnareable, rootable.  Have a few druids/rangers well heck anyone kite some of the adds as you kill off the mobs.  Keep a very close eye on the general since he has the ability to warp at times.  As well do NOT agro him at all while he is under water (he is at certain points), that can cause the entire war to just poof on you.  I can not emphasize enough from what I have heard from other people that is the real thing, keep kos people away totally if they are there, but do not agro while underwater!  Again 10 people would be the ideal simple number I would recommend, but I also recommend bringing extra for just in case.  A cleric or 2, and an enchanter and one warriror is the min of key classes. <p>The Mismatched Cleric <br>
Officer of Fury's edge<br>
-Xazy<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/unoonievioletskies.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoonieVioletskies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>QHills and Clueless</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/1/02 9:24:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=352.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 8th Shawl</span><hr size=1> get a good group of well equiped 60s who arent kos to coldain.<br>
<br>
or, get 2 groups of 55+ who arent kos to coldain.<br>
<br>
when i did it i had 13 people, average level was prob like 57. it was fairly easy. <br>
make sure you have an enchanter, they are a huge help in this battle. <p><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" background="http://www.sebminas.com/eq/sig.jpg" width="490"><tr><td style=filter:glow(color="0080FF") valign="top"  height="10"><font size="3"><br><br>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp<a style="font-weight:bold ;color:FFE8E8; text-decoration: none" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=33330">Noonie Violetskies</a></font></td></tr><tr><td height="116" valign="top"><font size="4" color="white"> <b>&nbspArch Mage of Thunderwalkers</b></font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/ubroomt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BrooMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>QHills and Clueless</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/1/02 11:30:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=352.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ....</span><hr size=1> Did it twice now, best idea is bring about 4-5 tanks and just tank me stuff, rangers can tank mez these as well seeing as they are pretty weak. Its a fun quest, send me a tell sometime if ya need a 60 war, i'd gladly give ya a hand. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/ulokar008.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lokar008</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karanas' Farmer</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/1/02 11:41:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=352.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ....</span><hr size=1> ive never done the quest so i really could be talking out my ass, but perhaps you could have a friendly chanter charm